## Implementation Guide

### Tab System Implementation

1. **Tab Navigation**:
   - Single-page application approach with tab switching
   - Active tab has visual indicator (background or underline)
   - Tab content loads only when selected (lazy loading)
   - URL parameter to deep link to specific tab: ?tab=overview|vehicle|sim|alerts|telemetry
   
2. **Data Loading Strategy**:
   - Load overview data on initial page load
   - Other tab data loads only when tab is selected
   - Implement caching for tab data to avoid repeated API calls
   - Show loading indicators during data fetching

3. **Responsive Design**:
   - On mobile: Stack all sections vertically
   - On tablet: Maintain tab navigation at top, adapt content layouts
   - On desktop: Show as designed

### API Integration

1. **Overview Tab**:
   - `GET /api/fleet/obd-devices/{id}/` (comprehensive device information)
   - `GET /api/fleet/obd-devices/{id}/communication-history/` (recent communications)
   
2. **Vehicle Tab**:
   - `GET /api/fleet/vehicles/{vehicle_id}/summary/` (simplified vehicle data)
   - `GET /api/fleet/vehicles/{vehicle_id}/latest_obd/` (current telemetry snapshot)
   
3. **SIM Card Tab**:
   - `GET /api/fleet/sim-cards/{sim_id}/summary/` (simplified SIM data)
   
4. **Alerts Tab**:
   - `GET /api/fleet/alerts/?device={id}&status=active&limit=3` (only most recent alerts)
   
5. **Telemetry Tab**:
   - `GET /api/fleet/obd-telemetry/?device={id}&limit=3` (only most recent data points)
